n| haat10    = 40\n| class10   = D\n| city10    = Saint Marys, Alaska\n| coord10   = {{coord|62|3|11.0|N|163|10|40.2|W|type:landmark}}\n| notes10   = <ref name=\"KSYU\"/>\n| call11   = KTYU\n| freq11   = 99.1\n| fid11    = 197861\n| watts11  = 7 [[Watt]]s\n| haat11   = 108.8\n| class11  = D\n| city11   = Tanana, Alaska\n| coord11  = {{coord|65|10|52.6|N|151|59|04.1|W|type:landmark}}\n| notes11  = <ref name=\"KTYU\"/>\n}}\n\n==Translator==\nIn addition to the main station, KIYU is relayed by an FM translator to widen its broadcast area.\n{{RadioTranslators\n| call1    = K241BE\n| freq1    = {{Frequency|[[96.1 FM]]|[[MHz]]}}\n| fid1     = 153359\n| watts1   = 6 [[Watt]]s\n| haat1    = 19\n| class1   = D\n| city1    = Saint Marys, Alaska\n| coord1   = {{coord|64|19|40|N|158|43|36|W|type:landmark}}\n| notes1   = <ref name=\"K241BE\"/>\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em|refs=\n<ref name=\"LaunchDate\">{{cite book|url=http://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-BC-YB/2010/D1-2010-BC-YB-7.pdf|title=Broadcasting Yearbook 2010|date=2010|accessdate=July 26, 2016|publisher=ProQuest, LLC/Reed Publishing (Nederland), B.V.|page=D-55}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Arbitron\">{{cite web|url=http://www1.arbitron.com/sip/displaySip.do?surveyID=SU16&band=am&callLetter=KIYU|title=Arbitron Station Information Profiles|accessdate=July 26, 2016|work=[[Nielsen Audio]]/[[Nielsen Holdings]]}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"FCC\">{{cite web|url=http://transition.fcc.gov/fcc-bin/amq?call=KIYU|title=KIYU Facility Record|accessdate=July 26, 2016|work=[[Federal Communications Commission]], audio division}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"KRFF\">{{cite web|url=http://www.krff891.com/?q=programming|title=Programming - krff891.com|accessdate=July 26, 2016|work=Athabascan Fiddlers Association, Inc.}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"KALG\">{{cite web|url=http://transition.fcc.gov/fcc-bin/fmq?call=KALG|title=KALG Facility Record|accessdate=July 26, 2016|work=[[Federal Communications Commission]], audio division}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"KAMN\">{{cite 