\"FCC\"/>\n\n==Rebroadcasters==\nIn addition to the main station, KIYU is relayed on 11 full-power FM repeaters to widen its broadcast area. KIYU programming is also simulcast on [[KRFF (FM)|KRFF]] in Fairbanks, weekdays from 1:00pm to 4:00pm.<ref name=\"KRFF\"/>\n{{RadioTranslators\n| call1    = KALG\n| freq1    = 98.1\n| fid1     = 178864\n| watts1   = 100 [[Watt]]s\n| haat1    = -77\n| class1   = D\n| city1    = Kaltag, Alaska\n| coord1   = {{coord|64|19|40|N|158|43|36|W|type:landmark}}\n| notes1   = <ref name=\"KALG\"/>\n| call2    = KAMN\n| freq2    = 98.1\n| fid2     = 180624\n| watts2   = 100 [[Watt]]s\n| haat2    = -47\n| class2   = D\n| city2    = Iliamna, Alaska\n| coord2   = {{coord|59|45|17|N|154|52|15|W|type:landmark}}\n| notes2   = <ref name=\"KAMN\"/>\n| call3    = KHUS\n| freq3    = 98.1\n| fid3     = 178866\n| watts3   = 36 [[Watt]]s\n| haat3    = 57\n| class3   = D\n| city3    = Huslia, Alaska\n| coord3   = {{coord|65|41|48|N|156|21|52|W|type:landmark}}\n| notes3   = <ref name=\"KHUS\"/>\n| call4    = KHUU\n| freq4    = 97.1\n| fid4     = 199395\n| watts4   = 87 [[Watt]]s\n| haat4    = -164\n| class4   = D\n| city4    = Hughes, Alaska\n| coord4   = {{coord|66|2|50|N|154|15|20|W|type:landmark}}\n| notes4   = <ref name=\"KHUU\"/>\n| call5    = KIYU-FM\n| freq5    = 88.1\n| fid5     = 178861\n| watts5   = 100 [[Watt]]s\n| haat5    = 15\n| class5   = D\n| city5    = Galena, Alaska\n| coord5   = {{coord|64|44|34|N|156|50|30|W|type:landmark}}\n| notes5   = <ref name=\"KIYU-FM\"/>\n| call6    = KKET\n| freq6    = 95.9\n| fid6     = 199490\n| watts6   = 99 [[Watt]]s\n| haat6    = -44.4\n| class6   = D\n| city6    = Allakaket, Alaska\n| coord6   = {{coord|66|33|53|N|152|38|38|W|type:landmark}}\n| notes6   = <ref name=\"KKET\"/>\n| call7    = KNUL\n| freq7    = 99.1\n| fid7     = 178863\n| watts7   = 100 [[Watt]]s\n| haat7    = 5\n| class7   = D\n| city7    = Nulato, Alaska\n| coord7   = {{coord|64|43|59|N|158|6|25|W|type:landmark}}\n| notes7   = <ref name=\